  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Advocacy coalition support</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">VEPR is coordinating organisation of the Coalition on Agriculture and Farmer&apos;s Welfare (Agriculture Coalition). With its professional staff and roster of experts that is strong in research and policy analysis, VEPR#s core roles in this project will be tocontribute to political economy analysis, policy research, and embedded advocacy with government and NA representatives.

As a country with along-standing rice farming history with fertile Mekong and Red River deltas, after its opening in 1986, Vietnamhas rapidly become the world#s second largest rice exporter. However, even with the position of a great rice export, rice farmers in Vietnam are still very poor and  Vietnam&apos;s rice business is still very ineffective.  Research done by the Agricultural Coalition in 2014 identified theproblems of Vietnam&apos;s rice market is caused by 1) unreasonable rice export policies in Decree 109 on rice export and (2) abusive role of the Vietnam Food Association (VFA), which has acted as an extension of the state ratherthan an authentic agricultural association that represents internal democracy, protection of interests of association members,  market research and development, internal quality cross-checking, brand development.

Therefore, from 1/4/2017-31/3/2018,  theCoalition sets the following focuses for its action plan:
# Building and sustaining an enabling environment and legal framework that promote fairer share of benefits and risks amongactors, especially those of farmers and SMEs (level playing field, sustainable rice value chains) # (Decree109)
# Creating an open and democratic space and processes for policy making for inclusive voices of the low-voices and transparency (Decree 109)
# Transforming VFA into a more accountable and transparent agriculture professional association (APO)
# Farmers and SMEs enterprises# authentic voices and representation are appropriately regulated and promoted in the operations of the reformed association (APO)
# AgriCo will also conduct training and workshop to build policy advocacy capacity for its members</narrative>
  </description>
